body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting CarDeals Support. My name is Dennis Ramirez and I'm here to assist you. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: It's nice to meet you, Donna. Could you please provide me with the VIN number of your vehicle for data verification?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five six seven eight four nine two one three zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Donna. One more piece of information I need is your email address. Could you share that with me, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing the requested information, Donna. We will investigate the data management issue related to your vehicle. Is there anything else you would like to add before we proceed?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now. I'm just surprised by the situation.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand your concern, Donna. We will work on resolving this promptly. Thank you for your time and patience. Have a good day!
